[1]
Date: Tue 25 May 2010
Source: Japan's MAFF web-site, daily FMD press release [trans.,
abridged, edited]
<http://www.maff.go.jp/j/press/syouan/douei/100525.html>


As of 25 May 2010, the number of confirmed outbreaks has risen to
201, involving a total of 147 894 animals including 19 720 cattle,
128 159 pigs, 7 goats and 8 sheep. There are several additional
suspected cases.

